<!-- PHILOSOPHY -->
<section id="philosophy">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <span class="section-num">02</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Teaching Philosophy</h2>
    <span class="section-line"></span>
  </div>
  <div class="philosophy-grid">
    <div class="philosophy-text reveal">
      <p>
        Every learner has the capacity to grow — the teacher's job is to find the right door. Whether in a school classroom, a student's home, or an online Zoom session with a child across the world, I bring the same structured, warm, and results-focused approach.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe that assessment is not a conclusion but a compass. Monthly tests aren't about grading students — they're about understanding where a child is and deciding where to take them next. This habit of reflection has driven measurable growth in every student I've worked with.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also believe deeply in keeping learning interactive. Students learn best when they are active participants, not passive recipients. I design my sessions to invite questions, curiosity, and genuine engagement — because the teacher who makes class feel like a conversation produces learners who never stop asking questions.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="values-list reveal">
      <div class="value-item">
        <h4>Assessment-Driven Growth</h4>
        <p>Regular monthly testing reveals what each student knows — and points clearly to what they need next. Data shapes every teaching decision.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item">
        <h4>Interactive Learning</h4>
        <p>The classroom, whether physical or virtual, is a dialogue. Students are welcomed to participate, question, and engage from every angle.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item">
        <h4>Adaptability Across Contexts</h4>
        <p>From nursery-level learners to GCSE candidates, and from in-person classrooms to Zoom — I adapt my style, pace, and tools to the student in front of me.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item">
        <h4>Consistency & Dedication</h4>
        <p>Great teaching requires showing up — even during national service. I commit to my students and honour that commitment regardless of circumstance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

